description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and skilled administrator to support the Public Health Team and Dental commissioning Team. The role will be based in Rotherham, although a flexible approach is required as a presence at meetings across the area will be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder should have good administration experience, preferably within a management or business support field, an excellent understanding of processes, lean or streamlined working, and be able to evidence experience of developing, embedding and supporting new systems and processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should have excellent IT skills with a sound knowledge and understanding of all Microsoft Office applications. Your skills will include excellent minute recording and an understanding of, or willingness to learn new areas of work as we seek to develop new systems to support efficient working practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a key member of the team whose overarching goal is to enable, promote and support the effective use of data, information, knowledge and technology to improve, inform and support a portfolio of projects, services, and initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would be useful, but not essential, for you to have some NHS experience. You will, above all, be enthusiastic, keen, and able to work on your own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sarah Hipkiss&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: sarah.hipkiss@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07730 379257&lt;/p&gt;
